<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0023" RecordId="021-000001571"><Name>Umoristi (Accademia degli)</Name><AlternativeName>Academia degli Humoristi|Academia dei begli Umori</AlternativeName><City CityId="45"><CityItalianName>Roma</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Rome</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Romae</CityLatinName></City><EmblemDescription>Rain falling from a cloud of vapour drawn from the sea by the sun</EmblemDescription><EmblemImage ImageId="54397">021-000001571_54397_1.jpg</EmblemImage><Motto>Redit agmine dulci</Motto><StartDate>ca.1600</StartDate><EndDate>ca.1670</EndDate><DateText>ca.1600-ca.1670</DateText><Notes>Salviani, Sarrocchia, Rinuccini, Aleandri, Gonzaga, Cardinal Caetani, Rossi, and P. della Valle, founded the Accademia degli Umoristi (see Piera Russo, `L`Accademia degli Umoristi`, in Esperienze Letterarie (1979). ---- Complete list of all publications on Theatre by Accademici Umoristi, is in Franchi, Drammaturgia romana (Rome, 1988). ---- An evaluation on the Academy`s interest for theatre, in Laura Alemanno, L`Accademia degli Umoristi, in Roma moderna e contemporanea, III (1995), 1, pp. 97-120. ---- Rime degli Accademici Umoristi (ms in Modena, Biblioteca Estense, Raccolta Campori 627 y H, 218 include contributions by Guarini, Paoli, di Somma, Preti, Leonida, Falconio, Sertini, Zagarini, Rinuccini, Caetano, Pascali, Querengo, Macedonio. ---- The description of an academic gathering is in John Evelyn`s Diary (15-17 February 1645). --- The presence of French scholars in the Academy is described by Francis W. Gravit, The Accademia degli Umoristi and its French Relationship (1934). Publication related to the Academy, but not included in in British Library catalogue, is: Capponi, Giovanni, I bombici: idillio dell`ostinato accad. umorista (Venetia: presso Triuisan Bertolotti, 1610).
